# Production RAG System

A production-grade Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) system with embeddings and vector storage.

## Progress

### ✅ Day 1 - Document Processing
- [x] Environment setup
- [x] OpenAI API integration
- [x] PDF document loader
- [x] Text chunking with overlap
- [x] Basic testing

### ✅ Day 2 - Embeddings & Vector Store
- [x] Embedding generation (OpenAI text-embedding-3-small)
- [x] ChromaDB vector store setup
- [x] Complete ingestion pipeline
- [x] Semantic search working
- [x] Data persistence verified

### 🔄 Day 3 - Retrieval & Question Answering
- [ ] Build retriever module
- [ ] Build QA generator
- [ ] Complete RAG system
- [ ] Basic UI

## Current Status

✅ **Full ingestion pipeline working!**
- Can load PDFs
- Split into chunks
- Generate embeddings
- Store in vector database
- Search by semantic similarity

**Stats from latest ingestion:**
- Documents: 3 PDFs
- Chunks: 51
- Embeddings: 1536 dimensions each
- Cost: ~$0.08
- Time: ~2 minutes

## Quick Start
```bash
# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Set up API key
echo "OPENAI_API_KEY=your-key" > .env

# Ingest documents
python src/ingestion_pipeline.py

# Test retrieval
python src/test_retrieval.py
```

## Architecture
```
PDF Documents
    ↓
Document Loader (PyPDF2)
    ↓
Text Chunker (500 words, 50 overlap)
    ↓
Embedding Generator (OpenAI API)
    ↓
Vector Store (ChromaDB)
    ↓
Semantic Search
```

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── document_loader.py      # PDF loading
├── text_chunker.py         # Document chunking
├── embeddings.py           # Embedding generation
├── vector_store.py         # ChromaDB interface
└── ingestion_pipeline.py   # Complete pipeline

tests/
└── test_day2.py           # Day 2 test suite

chroma_db/                 # Persistent vector database
```